<!-- This class handles the about page, which displays the purpose of the application,
     the tools used to create it, and any packages/dependencies that come with the application -->

<!-- Adds header to page -->
<%- include("partials/header") %>



<div class="container">
    <h1>About Page</h1>
    <div class="About">
        <div class= "Purpose">
            <h2>What is the purpose?</h2>
            <p>
                Welcome to Accomodate, this website allows users to sign up, post accomodations
                from around the world and leave comments on such locations.         
            </p>
            <div class= "Github">    
                <a href="https://github.com/ConnorM1998/Accomodate"><h3>GitHub Link!</h3></a>
            </div>  
        </div>
        <div class= "Tools">
            <h2>Tools Used:</h2>
            <a href="https://nodejs.org/en/about/"><h3>Node.js</h3></a>
            <p>
                Node.js made up the backend of the application         
            </p>   
            <a href="https://nodejs.org/en/about/"><h3>Bootstrap</h3></a>
            <p>
                A toolkit that helped style and make the application responsive (to resizing)       
            </p>       
            <a href="https://www.mongodb.com/"><h3>MongoDB</h3></a>
            <p>
                Allowed for the storage of Accomodations/Users/Comments into databases.
                Used for Local Development        
            </p>   
            <a href="https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas"><h3>MongoDB Atlas</h3></a>
            <p>
                Allowed for MongoDB databases to be stored in cloud, allowing for easy integration
                with the heroku server.          
            </p>  
            <a href="https://www.heroku.com/about"><h3>Heroku</h3></a>
            <p>
                Used to deploy the application giving it its own server, allowing access from anywhere         
            </p>     
        </div>
        <div class= "Dependencies">
            <h2>Packages/Dependencies:</h2>
            <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/body-parser"><h3>Body-Parser</h3></a>
            <p>
                Provides a middleware that parses incoming request bodies before the handlers     
            </p>    
            <a href="https://ejs.co/"><h3>EJS</h3></a>
            <p>
                EJS allowed for the generation of HTML markup with plain JavaScript.     
            </p> 
            <a href="https://expressjs.com/"><h3>Express.js</h3></a>
            <p>
                Express.js is a web framework that handled routing on the website. Also <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/express-session">express-sesion</a> helped
                with giving a user a specific session, e.g. when logged in.      
            </p> 
            <a href="https://mongoosejs.com/"><h3>Mongoose</h3></a>
            <p>
                Provided a schema-based solution to modeling application data       
            </p>           
            <a href="http://www.passportjs.org/"><h3>Passport</h3></a>
            <p>
                An authentication middleware that works with express, handles the creation of 
                user accounts. Allows for username/password authentication.  <a href="http://www.passportjs.org/packages/passport-local/">passport-local</a> aswell as
                <a href="https://github.com/saintedlama/passport-local-mongoose">passport-local-mongoose</a> were used to increase functionality/support
            </p>         
            <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/method-override"><h3>Method-Override</h3></a>
            <p>
                Allows for the overriding of METHOD verbs, i.e. POST overriden to PUT METHOD
            </p>                        

        </div>
    </div>
</div>




<!-- Adds footer to page -->
<%- include("partials/footer") %>
